title: Grateful Dead Live at Manor Downs on 1981-07-04
lineage: Cassette Master (Nakamichi DR-1) > Korg MR-1000 (1-bit/5.6MHz) > Audiogate (1-bit/5.6MHz > 16-bit/44.1kHz) > cdwav (edits)
description:
Set 1

Jack Straw, Peggy-O, Me & My Uncle-> Big River, Loser, Little Red Rooster, Tennessee Jed-> Minglewood Blues, China Cat Sunflower-> I Know You Rider

Set 2

Feel Like A Stranger, Bird Song-> Playin' In The Band-> Drums-> Not Fade Away-> Wharf Rat-> Sugar Magnolia, E: One More Saturday Night

reviews.review_text: Download this version! Wow what presence. Great recording!  Download this one!

Flight of the seabirds.... Always loved those "seagulls" in the Playin' jam.

Never heard Bobby do anything like that before or since.

I'll bet a good time was had by all....

Independence Day Spectacular This show was played on the day I was born.  I revisit it on or near my birthday most years.  This is some great early 80s Dead!  

The crowd erupts when "leaving Texas, Fourth day of July" is changed to "T for Texas, T for the Fourth of July".  Weather was a steamy 94°

Thanks to all!

30 Years 2 Days Ago What a long strange trip This always been a very memorable show for Me.Saturday night 4th of July.Great sets, spectacular fireworks. I bought a dozen tickets, & took 9 close friends to Their first show. Left 2 at "Will Call" under the name of Pigpen just in case. Married My sweetheart two years later at the Labor Day show 8-31-1985.

I Was There!  I Was There!
After spending he afternoon jumping off a 75 foot cliff into the crack through the llano batholith into the Edwards Aquafer at the historic location of the Earliest Mormon colony in Texas 'Mormon Mills' in Marble Falls Tex.(it was a campground then, now you can only see it from satellite photos :-{ ) We all decided to go to Manor downs for GD and 4th of July. AWESOME!!! is not a word I use Lightly or often but altered awareness from the product of cow pies ;-} and fireworks with "Jerry and The Gang" Jamming is something I will never forget! I did not follow them in later year like so many (wish I could have!) but I caught a few shows and all I can say is It was Grateful Dead and it was sooo! goood! I was there and I'm a Grateful Head!!!
